<dl id="n12213l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12213l">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12213l"> 213(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> funeral games <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n12213l"> <li>FW prototext </li><li><ms href="#n12213l">MS BL 47482b-86</ms> </li><li>JJA 58:047 <a name="rA2d" href="../../ff/fdra/rda.htm#rA2d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/r/rA2d.htm#n12213l">Draft: III&sect;3A.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">En dehors des r&eacute;citations po&eacute;tiques, la comm&eacute;moration des h&eacute;ros comportait des jeux; c&apos;est qu&apos;aux jeux que se r&eacute;duit, &agrave; notre connaissance l&apos;&eacute;l&eacute;ment dramatique des f&ecirc;tes irlandaises. <br><font color="green">[Apart from poetic recitations, the <mark>commemoration of heroes involved games</mark>; as far as we know the dramatic element of Irish festivals was restricted to these games]</font> <small> Stefan Czarnowski, <a name="SCSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SCSP"><cite title="source">Le culte des h&eacute;ros et ses conditions sociale: saint Patrick, h&eacute;ros nationale de l'Irlande</cite></a> (1919) LI</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n12177l" href="n12all.htm#n12177l">N12 (VI.B.14):177(l)</a> and <a name="n11137b" href="n11all.htm#n11137b">N11 (VI.B.5):137(b)</a>: &lsquo;funeral sports&rsquo; only in first insertion, changed to &lsquo;funeral games&rsquo; in 3A.2+ </mm> </dd></dl>
